 - modular exponential
 - adding, subtracting, multiplication, divide in the form of a string
 - Chinese remainder thoerem
 - binary search (monotonicity)
 - segment trees 
   they can do everything what BI tree can do but takes a memory of n = 2^x 
 - binary indexed trees
   they represent number as a power of 2 and in some cases can be highly useful
